The Kenya Ports Authority hosted the annual stakeholders' luncheon at Radisson Blu on Wednesday. As an authority mandated to facilitate trade, KPA held the event to dialogue and to keep strategising on picking and embracing best trade and business practices, not only for the country but also for the region. Present were KPA board chairman Gen (Rtd) Joseph Kibwana, MD Daniel Manduku, Transport CS James Macharia, African Development Bank DG Gabriel Negatu and businessman and philanthropist Manu Chandaria.